: What if the Germans had won WWII?</span><hr size=1> Actually Hitler did support the development of a nuclear bomb,  <br>
Nazi Germany made every effort to develop an atomic bomb,<br>
but fortunately the effort was mis-managed.  There were 3 seperate<br>
teams working on the 'bomb' in Germany and rather than share information, <br>
they treated it as a competition... which is one of the reason's they failed.<br>
<br>
The only way Germany could have one the Second World War is IF they had <br>
developed atomic weapons years before the US did... say 1943. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/18/02 11:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What if the Germans had won WWII?</span><hr size=1> That's just as bad, or good rather. We were rather fortunate that the Nazis were so incompetent. Oh, could you provide links to the Nazi bomb program? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 568<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/18/02 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What if the Germans had won WWII?</span><hr size=1> I knew Von Braun had a lot of lofty dreams of getting to the Moon and Mars but I didn't know he wanted to build a space station first.  The Germans definately had the most advanced technology at the time and could have pulled off those stunts a lot earlier.  While engineers and scientists were still building toy rockets in Allied countries the Nazis were sending full fledged beasts with 50,000 pounds of thrust across the English channel.  The Russian and American space programs were both built largely upon German technology.  The Germans probably would have advanced a lot faster in space to considering that they didn't exactly have a lot of ethical barriers in place when it came to human experimentation.  Imagine all of those poor souls who would be pulled from the camps and experimented on in order to learn how to survive in space. <br>
