<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>June 3, 1940. Harteck reports on a uranium oxide-dry ice reactor. His 185 kilograms of uranium is inadequate for neutron multiplication, but Heisenberg's group in Dahlem refuses to share more of the available uranium; Heisenberg's Leipzig project has first claim on available heavy water.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
