until Japan developed their own 'bomb'. At the first opportunity,<br>
the Nazis would break any treaty... just ask the Russians. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/24/02 10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> germany could not have won.  by the time the americans came...at the german high water mark, people were starving, 50 million people were left at home...it would be impossible to control the world.  they didnt even have carriers to send a-bombs to the us.  we would have always been a threat to them...they would have lost in the end. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1701<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 1:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> If England had been conquered by Germany, it would have deprived<br>
the US bases from which to launch the bombing raids on German<br>
industry.  <br>
<br>
With Englands defeat so goes the Allies access to advanced jet<br>
engines.  Leaving only Germany with jet fighters.  The US could<br>
build ultra long range bombers, but without the much needed<br>
fighter escort, thus loses would be unacceptable, especially<br>
at the hands of more advanced jet fighters.<br>
<br>
Carriers would not have been needed to bomb the US in this<br>
hypothetical history, Germany would have used the follow up<br>
to the V2 rocket, the A9/10 to deliver nukes to the Eastern<br>
coast of the US.<br>
<br>
Germany would possess weapons of mass destruction and the<br>
means to deliver them worldwide by 1950.<br>
<br>
The US would be isolated and of no threat to the Greater <br>
German Reich. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 585<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 6:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/Bart-term.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> The kiss of death for the Germans was invading the USSR later than they planned and getting bogged down in the Russian winter and becoming ensnared in a multiple front war against the Soviets.  If Hitler had defeated Stalin and then turned everything he had on England history might have been different.  I sometimes wonder how things might have turned out if Hitler had convinced the Japanese to use their Naval might against the English early in the war.  The Japanese slaughtered the British fleets in the South Pacific and would have been more than a match for the English anywhere else.  They could have blockaded the island and essentially starved it to death.  Fortunately the Japanese made the tactical mistake of attacking the USA early on and the Nazis of invading Russia too late in the year and the rest is history.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaphod4468>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1707<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 9:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> I hope no one misunderstands the post.  I don't sympathise<br>
with the Nazis at all.  I'm fascinated with the 'What if'<br>
scenarios, and this is a classic.  But to take it further,<br>
past the war, and into the modern day, what kind of presence<br>
would humanity have in space? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/26/02 9:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> zaphod, the v2 was a long way off from what they would need to hit the US.  <br>
<br>
second, the germans were never really all that close to getting the a-bomb.  and even if japan hadnt attacked us, we would have gotten the a-bomb first, because of the existing american fear of german rockets.  <br>
<br>
germany really could not win a war against the US.  they would not have had the troops.  we could have made a german landing far worse for them than they made D-Day for us.  by that time, Germany was fighting on 2 fronts.  granted, they had more troops on our front (despite what many people say, the Russians did not have the juice left to launch an offensive until the americans had already entered germany), but they were still spread thin.  americans would have been fresh on our soil, and fighting on 1 front.  <br>
<br>
the japanese didnt have the manpower to launch a land invasion of the US either...navally, they might have won.  but i doubt they could have ever breached the coast of California.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 593<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/27/02 1:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Actually, Hitler had some super weapons</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I hope no one misunderstands the post. I don't sympathise with the Nazis at all. I'm fascinated with the 'What if' scenarios, and this is a classic. But to take it further, past the war, and into the modern day, what kind of presence would humanity have in space?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
